args:
The tear closes, trapping Phraeganoth inside the
space between worlds forever. With the battle
fought and won, everyone descends the
mountain in a celebratory mood—including
Celliera and Pele.
The tear collapses, stranding Phraeganoth in the\nspace between worlds.
Naught remains of it save the beast's furious roar,\nwhich echoes throughout the cavern.
He's trapped inside that place for good.\nWe've won.
As the last of the black mana streaming through\nthe tear fades, King Archeole crumbles to dust.
You have earned your rest, my king.\nI pray you might find peace at last.
Now that the black mana is gone,\nthe volcano's mana is back to normal.
We needn't fear an eruption now.
Plus, it looks like all the fiends've been\ncleaned out.
The villagers down below should be able\nto go about their lives in safety now.
We should head back down ourselves.
What will you do now, Pele?
I will take time to mourn my king—\nand the fallen people of Alba.
You've been away from this world a long\ntime, so why not enjoy it? You're the last\nAlban who can, after all.
And do come visit the Halidom if your\ntravels take you near us.
Once I have taken the time to grieve,\nI shall certainly stop by.
In the meantime, know that you have my\nsincerest thanks.
I will never forget the debt I owe you.
Well, guess I should be going if—
Uh oh. We got an incomin' horde'a folks.\nAnd they're wavin' their arms like maniacs.
We'll never let a fiend send us running\nscared again! We swear!
And panicked or no, I feel just AWFUL\nabout slapping your hand away!
Then...you don't hate me?\nYou weren't running from me?
Yeah! I mean, you're crazy strict and all,\nbut you're twice as nice!
There's not a one among us who doesn't\nrespect you to the end, ma'am.
Yes, I couldn't be more proud of... Wait no!\nI'm not proud at ALL! My students turned\nand ran at the sight of a fiend!
That won't do at all! Time to break the lot\nof you down and build you up from scratch!

The training camp is a do-over—and day
one starts NOW! Get running, and don't
stop till you hit that caldera! LEFT, RIGHT!
LEFT, RIGHT! LEFT, RIGHT!
It seems this is goodbye for now,\n{player_name}.
I'll be by your castle to properly thank you\nonce I've seen to these pups.
To thank me? What did I do?
You gave me more courage than you know.\nYour words meant the world to me.
I expect they'll keep me going for quite\nsome time to come.
So yes, I plan to thank you somehow.\nLook forward to it!
...I have a favor to ask of you all.
If anyone has any criticism or complaints\nfor me, I hope you won't hold back.
And where is this coming from?
Just something that's been on my mind.
Ha ha! Well, I am happy to lay any worries\nto a quick rest.
I've always spoken my mind frankly to you.\nEven far exceeded my station to chew you\nout once or twice.
Yeah, we ain't the type to hold back just\n'cause yer a prince. I couldn't fight with ya\nif I thought I had to walk on eggshells.
We are. And you're right—we HAVE all\nbeen pretty frank with each other.
(I've never stopped to notice it,\nbut I really am lucky.)
Okay, you're being weird and I don't like it.
Ha! I NEVER had to worry with you, Notte.\nNow come on. ...Let's go home.
